  "root_text": {
    "sn35.157:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 35.157 ",
    "sn35.157:0.2": "16. Nandikkhayavagga ",
    "sn35.157:0.3": "Bāhiranandikkhayasutta ",
    "sn35.157:1.1": "“Anicceyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpe aniccāti passati, sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi. ",
    "sn35.157:1.2": "Sammā passaṁ nibbindati. ",
    "sn35.157:1.3": "Nandikkhayā rāgakkhayo; ",
    "sn35.157:1.4": "rāgakkhayā nandikkhayo. ",
    "sn35.157:1.5": "Nandirāgakkhayā cittaṁ suvimuttanti vuccati. ",
    "sn35.157:1.6": "Anicceyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sadde … ",
    "sn35.157:1.7": "gandhe … ",
    "sn35.157:1.8": "rase … ",
    "sn35.157:1.9": "phoṭṭhabbe … ",
    "sn35.157:1.10": "dhamme aniccāti passati, sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi. ",
    "sn35.157:1.11": "Sammā passaṁ nibbindati. ",
    "sn35.157:1.12": "Nandikkhayā rāgakkhayo; ",
    "sn35.157:1.13": "rāgakkhayā nandikkhayo. ",
    "sn35.157:1.14": "Nandirāgakkhayā cittaṁ suvimuttanti vuccatī”ti. ",
    "sn35.157:1.15": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn35.157:0.1": "Linked Discourses 35.157 ",
    "sn35.157:0.2": "16. The End of Relishing ",
    "sn35.157:0.3": "The Exterior and the End of Relishing ",
    "sn35.157:1.1": "“Mendicants, sights really are impermanent. A mendicant sees that they are impermanent: that’s their right view. ",
    "sn35.157:1.2": "Seeing rightly, they grow disillusioned. ",
    "sn35.157:1.3": "When relishing ends, greed ends. When greed ends, relishing ends. ",
    "sn35.157:1.4": "",
    "sn35.157:1.5": "When relishing and greed end, the mind is said to be well freed. ",
    "sn35.157:1.6": "Sounds … ",
    "sn35.157:1.7": "Smells … ",
    "sn35.157:1.8": "Tastes … ",
    "sn35.157:1.9": "Touches … ",
    "sn35.157:1.10": "Ideas really are impermanent. A mendicant sees that they are impermanent: that’s their right view. ",
    "sn35.157:1.11": "Seeing rightly, they grow disillusioned. ",
    "sn35.157:1.12": "When relishing ends, greed ends. When greed ends, relishing ends. ",
    "sn35.157:1.13": "",
    "sn35.157:1.14": "When relishing and greed end, the mind is said to be well freed.” "
  },
